      "content": "Yes, that makes sense. You're feeling a sense of disconnection and isolation, even in the midst of constant digital interaction. It's a feeling of being invisible, like you're just a faint glow in a sea of screens and faces. It's a common experience for those who spend most of their time staring at screens, and it's a reflection of the increasingly virtual nature of our lives.",
